pr_body:
During Google Summer of Code 2023, [Epoptes Improvements](https://ellak.gr/wiki/index.php?title=Google_Summer_of_Code_2023_proposed_ideas#Epoptes_improvements) was accepted as one of the project ideas of the the [Open Technologies Alliance (GFOSS)](https://summerofcode.withgoogle.com/programs/2023/organizations/open-technologies-alliance-gfoss) organization. Many thanks to both Google and GFOSS for supporting open source
development!

This PR includes the upstreamable parts of the GSoC 2023 "Epoptes Improvements" project.

Resolves:

- Should allow configure port range for incoming VNC connections to teachers computer ([#11](https://github.com/epoptes/epoptes/issues/11))
- Alias not saved when clicking "ok" ([#30](https://github.com/epoptes/epoptes/issues/30))
- Have lts.conf-assigned computer names shown even when client is off ([#38](https://github.com/epoptes/epoptes/issues/38))
- Set WoL when there's no IP ([#186](https://github.com/epoptes/epoptes/issues/186))
- Drop /etc/default/epoptes* scripts ([#187](https://github.com/epoptes/epoptes/issues/187))
- server.crt is blank ([#194](https://github.com/epoptes/epoptes/issues/194))
- No Processor information for rpi4 ([#200](https://github.com/epoptes/epoptes/issues/200))
- Better GPU information ([#201](https://github.com/epoptes/epoptes/issues/201))

New features:

- Adds support for new distributions: tested Fedora, CentOS Linux, CentOS Stream, Sangoma Linux, openSUSE Leap, Manjaro Linux, Arch Linux
- Automatic firewall configuration for ufw (e.g. Ubuntu) and firewalld (e.g. Fedora)

Work started, but not ready for upstream, so not included in this PR:

- Rewrite epoptes client in python
- Implement client details view for health monitoring
- Research for Wayland support
- Research for systemd socket activation
- Research FTBS after build ([#202](https://github.com/epoptes/epoptes/issues/202))

During Google Summer of Code 2023, [Epoptes Improvements](https://ellak.gr/wiki/index.php?title=Google_Summer_of_Code_2023_proposed_ideas#Epoptes_improvements) was accepted as one of the project ideas of the the [Open Technologies Alliance (GFOSS)](https://summerofcode.withgoogle.com/programs/2023/organizations/open-technologies-alliance-gfoss) organization. Many thanks to both Google and GFOSS for supporting open source
development!

This PR includes the upstreamable parts of the GSoC 2023 "Epoptes Improvements" project.

Resolves:

- Should allow configure port range for incoming VNC connections to teachers computer ([#11](https://github.com/epoptes/epoptes/issues/11))
- Alias not saved when clicking "ok" ([#30](https://github.com/epoptes/epoptes/issues/30))
- Have lts.conf-assigned computer names shown even when client is off ([#38](https://github.com/epoptes/epoptes/issues/38))
- Set WoL when there's no IP ([#186](https://github.com/epoptes/epoptes/issues/186))
- Drop /etc/default/epoptes* scripts ([#187](https://github.com/epoptes/epoptes/issues/187))
- server.crt is blank ([#194](https://github.com/epoptes/epoptes/issues/194))
- No Processor information for rpi4 ([#200](https://github.com/epoptes/epoptes/issues/200))
- Better GPU information ([#201](https://github.com/epoptes/epoptes/issues/201))

New features:

- Adds support for new distributions: tested Fedora, CentOS Linux, CentOS Stream, Sangoma Linux, openSUSE Leap, Manjaro Linux, Arch Linux
- Automatic firewall configuration for ufw (e.g. Ubuntu) and firewalld (e.g. Fedora)

Work started, but not ready for upstream, so not included in this PR:

- Rewrite epoptes client in python
- Implement client details view for health monitoring
- Research for Wayland support
- Research for systemd socket activation
- Research FTBS after build ([#202](https://github.com/epoptes/epoptes/issues/202))
